"{\"uid\": \"lemonde.fr-en-france-article-2024-04-26-paris-2024-france-plans-6-000-police-to-secure-olympic-torch-arrival_6669644_7.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Date:Loading date...  Time:Loading time...  Europeans stunned and challenged by new US security strategy  A mere trickle of Gazans allowed to evacuate to Europe  'The Voice of Hind Rajab' is more than a film about a child killed in Gaza  ICC member states seek to calm US concerns  Bosnia and Herzegovina's Serb entity elects ally of  former leader Dodik  In France's Somme, bagpipers keep the memory of the Great War alive  Latvia: Public mobilization grows in support of treaty for preventing violence against women  After Charlie Kirk's murder, Europe's far right swears allegiance to Trump's politics  'Decapitated bodies, death threats, that's our daily life': Tennis players, helpless targets of angry gamblers  Inside a major investigation into tennis match fixing linked to gambling  Survival of French drug consumption rooms hinges on social security budget  On France's coast, far-right British activists try to stop migrant crossings  Israel's D9 bulldozer, a tool of destruction in Gaza  Ukraine's Pokrovsk faces fierce fighting, footage analyzed by Le Monde reveals  Afghanistan: Relentless repression continues over four years into Taliban's rule  Watch: Hundreds of thousands march in France against budget cuts  'Never have we communicated so much without actually speaking to one another'  'The Trump-Infantino farce shows how FIFA debases football'  France's 1905 law separating churches and state: An irreplaceable compass  Asma Mhalla, political scientist: 'Peter Thiel embeds AI in a worldview where conflict and the state of emergency become virtues'  The lawyer suing far-right French mayors for setting up Nativity scenes  100 years of the photobooth: Meet the people keeping them alive  Iran's independent cinema in full revolt: 'With Woman, Life, Freedom, a major barrier was broken'  The first time Le Monde wrote about Jeffrey Epstein  Five spots in Paris to enjoy a (great) plant-based sandwich  Bayonne's 'Little Louvre,' the Bonnat-Helleu Museum, reopens after 14 years  Victor Hugo's interior architecture on display in Paris  A stroll through Cachan: From a royal aqueduct to a panoramic garden  Le Monde with AFP  1 min read  Some 6,000 police will be deployed next month to secure the arrival of the Olympic torch, which will travel from Greece to the southern French city of Marseille, French Interior Minister G\\u00e9rald Darmanin said on Friday, April 26.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 84, \"end\": 86, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.577056189794151, \"rank\": 0.7294199911234267, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 232, \"end\": 236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9962305571066122, \"rank\": 0.0037837053544151514, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 238, \"end\": 241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Criminal_Court\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.245005978761567e-13, \"text\": \"ICC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Criminal_Court\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Criminal_Court\"}, {\"begin\": 269, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.577056189794151, \"rank\": 0.7294199911234267, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 282, \"end\": 288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bosnian_War\", \"score\": 0.999807066242